The leaders of the ruling All Progressives Congress (APC), who include members of the National Working Committee (APC), led by the national chairman, Abdulahi Adamu, as well as APC governors on Tuesday stormed Ado-Ekiti, for mega rally for the party’s candidate in the June 18 governorship election.
The governors participating in the mega rally include the host, Governor Kayode Fayemi of Ekiti State, Governor Sanwo-Olu of Lagos State, Governor Dapo Abiodun of Ogun State, Governor Solomon Lalong of Plateau State,  Governor Umar Ganduje of Kano State, including the northern APC governors, and some seven other APC governors who held an urgent meeting President Muhammadu Buhari at the State House, Abuja on Tuesday morning.
